                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>St. Thomas</placeName>, <date>21st Jan\n                1866</date>.</p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">Shortly after the date of<lb/> my last, <date>17th</date> ult, I had\n                the pleasure of re<lb/>ceiving your valued lines of <date>4th</date> ult. I am\n                hap<lb/>py to reply that during the last two months<lb/> peace has prevailed among\n                us. Previously<lb/> we had enjoyed it between two and three<lb/> years, when\n                unfortunately it was interrupt<lb/>ed, and a secular paper was made the vehi<lb/>cle\n                for placing all the supposed grievances of<lb/> the congregation before the eyes of\n                strangers.<lb/> Those really interested in the welfare of the<lb/> Jewish name left\n                the claimants to reform<lb/> all the benefit thereof (if they could find any<lb/> in\n                it) but when a new field was opened, thro'<lb/> the Jewish press, publishing such\n                gross misstate<lb/>ments as would lead our brethren to believe<lb/> that the\n                religious agitation now prevalent is<lb/> felt all over the world to be requisite\n                for the</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3d795x4n/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
