                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>a show of religion he was not a popular man,<lb/> notwithstanding his learning\n                besides. <persName>Mr. Car<lb/>dose</persName> suggests that you should make\n                known<lb/> thro' the Occident your sentiments regarding<lb/> his conduct in the\n                disavowal <del>o</del>of his religion. <persName>Mr.<lb/> C.</persName> requested me\n                also to offer his regards to you.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have none of the plain Bibles of $2 ½ on<lb/> hand. Please send me\n                by first opportunity a<lb/> Daily Prayer Book, <hi rend=\"underline\">good</hi> paper\n                and elegantly<lb/> bound, with the name <persName>Mrs. David\n                Piza</persName>.—Per<lb/>haps you will be pleased to learn that I hope<lb/> to enter\n                the marriage state during next mo.<lb/> probably on <date>Monday evening 12th\n                    Adar</date>, the<lb/> young lady being a cousin of mine, <persName>Rachel<lb/>\n                    Piza</persName>. I was formerly one of those who ridiculed<lb/> the idea of\n                Israelites so generally marrying their<lb/> own relatives, but it seems to be the\n                happy fate<lb/> of <placeName>Israel</placeName> since their forefather of this name\n                set<lb/> the example not to mention his predecessors.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Anticipating the pleasure of soon hear<lb/>ing from you again</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">I remain, Rev. and dear Sir,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(9)\">Truly yours</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(10)\"><persName role=\"author\">David M. Piza</persName>.</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
